Body.Content:
Please join us for the monthly meeting of the technical leads from the professional schools, museums/galleries, libraries and other distributed technology units. 

 

People Hub and Grouper will be the featured topics for the March 21 3pm meeting (at the new CTL offices!)  This is planned as a working discussion -- please bring specific examples and use cases for ways you need to access people information.  Feel free to extend the meeting invite to developers in your shop who can contribute to the conversation. 

 

Plus our regular News & Notes sharing of topical items from each of your areas.

 

Please check our Basecamp discussion forum for the monthly agenda and location.  To add topics to the agenda please post to the Basecamp forum or contact Randall.rode@yale.edu .
